e rate that represents the whole date range.","pos":[9857,9990],"source":"Set the **singleRateForDateRange** property to **true** if the service can return a single rate that represents the whole date range."},{"content":"For example, you can use this setting to return a single exchange rate that represents the average exchange rate for a month.","pos":[9991,10116]},{"content":"If the service doesn’t support this functionality, set this property to <bpt id=\"p1\">**</bpt>false<ept id=\"p1\">**</ept>.","pos":[10117,10199],"source":" If the service doesn’t support this functionality, set this property to **false**."},{"content":"Implement the <bpt id=\"p1\">**</bpt>GetConfigurationDefaults<ept id=\"p1\">**</ept> method.","pos":[10668,10718],"source":"Implement the **GetConfigurationDefaults** method."},{"content":"Configuration defaults are name-value pairs that represent the default configuration settings for the exchange rate provider.","pos":[10719,10844]},{"content":"These settings are automatically loaded when the provider is registered, but the user can change them.","pos":[10845,10947]},{"content":"Take the required precautions when you convert these strings into usable values.","pos":[10948,11028]},{"content":"The value field is stored as an encrypted field in SQL.","pos":[11029,11084]},{"content":"Therefore, sensitive data such as an application programming interface (API) key will be more secure.","pos":[11085,11186]},{"content":"Implement the <bpt id=\"p1\">**</bpt>ValidateConfigurationDetail<ept id=\"p1\">**</ept> method.","pos":[11958,12011],"source":"Implement the **ValidateConfigurationDetail** method."},{"content":"This method enables the exchange rate provider to validate the configuration information that the user modified on the <bpt id=\"p1\">**</bpt>Configure exchange rate providers<ept id=\"p1\">**</ept> page.","pos":[12012,12174],"source":" This method enables the exchange rate provider to validate the configuration information that the user mod