lue<ept id=\"p1\">**</ept> method on that interface will provide the string representation of the property value for the property key that is provided.","pos":[14586,14745],"source":" A call to the **GetPropertyValue** method on that interface will provide the string representation of the property value for the property key that is provided."},{"content":"Take the required precautions when you convert this string value to another type.","pos":[14746,14827]},{"content":"Do any required validation up front.","pos":[14836,14872]},{"content":"For example, OANDA requires that an API key be supplied on every service call.","pos":[14873,14951]},{"content":"If this API key isn't set, the service will fail.","pos":[14952,15001]},{"content":"Verify that the API key isn't set, and exit early to receive an appropriate error message.","pos":[15002,15092]},{"content":"Some providers require explicit currency pairs when exchange rates are requested.","pos":[15101,15182]},{"content":"These providers are the same providers that set the <bpt id=\"p1\">**</bpt>IExchangeRateProviderSupportedOptions.doesSupportSpecificCurrencyPairs<ept id=\"p1\">**</ept> property to <bpt id=\"p2\">**</bpt>true<ept id=\"p2\">**</ept>.","pos":[15183,15331],"source":" These providers are the same providers that set the **IExchangeRateProviderSupportedOptions.doesSupportSpecificCurrencyPairs** property to **true**."},{"content":"In this case, you must use the currency pairs that the <bpt id=\"p1\">**</bpt>IExchangeRateRequest<ept id=\"p1\">**</ept> interface provides to drive the retrieval process.","pos":[15332,15462],"source":" In this case, you must use the currency pairs that the **IExchangeRateRequest** interface provides to drive the retrieval process."},{"content":"The OANDA provider implementation that follows shows a good example of this type of provider.","pos":[15463,15556]},{"content":"Typically, providers that don't support specific currency pairs return data for a fixed set of currency pairs.","pos":[15557,15667]},{"content":"In this case, the currency pairs that the <bpt id=\"p1\">**</bpt>IExchangeRateRequest<ept id=\"p1\">**</ept> interface provides can be ignored.","pos":[15668,15769],"source":" In this case, the currency pairs that the **IExchangeRateRequest** interface provides can be ignored."},{"content":"Providers should return all the rates that are available, and the framework will then import the correct rates, based on the user’s decision about whether to automatically create the required currency pairs.","pos":[15770,15977]},{"content":"The CentralBankOfEuropeProvider provider is a good example of this type of provider.","pos":[15978,16062]},{"content":"The <bpt id=\"p1\">**</bpt>IExchangeRateRequest<ept id=\"p1\">**</ept> interface has a property that is named <bpt id=\"p2\">**</bpt>ImportDateType<ept id=\"p2\">**</ept>.","pos":[16071,16158],"source":"The **IExchangeRateRequest** interface has a property that is named **ImportDateType**."},{"content":"This property indicates the dates that should be used to retrieve exchange rates from the service.","pos":[16159,16257]},{"content":"The two values that are available are <bpt id=\"p1\">**</bpt>CurrentDate<ept id=\"p1\">**</ept> and <bpt id=\"p2\">**</bpt>DateRange<ept id=\"p2\">**</ept>.","pos":[16258,16330],"source":" The two values that are available are **CurrentDate** and **DateRange**."},{"content":"<bpt id=\"p1\">**</bpt>CurrentDate<ept id=\"p1\">**</ept> retrieves the most current exchange rate from the exchange rate service.","pos":[16343,16431],"source":"**CurrentDate** retrieves the most current exchange rate from the exchange rate service."},{"content":"When this value is passed to the provider, the framework also sets <bpt id=\"p1\">**</bpt>IExchangeRateRequest.FromDate<ept id=\"p1\">**</ept> and <bpt id=\"p2\">**</bpt>IExchangeRateRequest.ToDate<ept id=\"p2\">**</ept> to the system date of the Application Object Server (AOS) computer that is making the request.","pos":[16432,1666