the correct date, because an exchange rate service might occasionally return rates for dates that weren't expected.","pos":[17735,17944]},{"content":"For example, if an exchange rate is requested for a date in the future, some providers return the most recent exchange rate instead of throwing an error or returning nothing.","pos":[17945,18119]},{"content":"If you encounter errors when you try to retrieve exchange rates from the exchange rate service, don't throw custom error messages.","pos":[18128,18258]},{"content":"The framework will alert the user that there is an issue by throwing generic error messages that state that the expected currency pairs could not be retrieved from the provider.","pos":[18259,18436]},{"content":"If you must log additional errors, use <bpt id=\"p1\">**</bpt>CurrencyEventSource<ept id=\"p1\">**</ept>.","pos":[18437,18500],"source":" If you must log additional errors, use **CurrencyEventSource**."},{"content":"For an example, see the <bpt id=\"p1\">**</bpt>catch<ept id=\"p1\">**</ept> statement and the <bpt id=\"p2\">**</bpt>if<ept id=\"p2\">**</ept> condition for the <bpt id=\"p3\">**</bpt>oandaKey<ept id=\"p3\">**</ept> variable in the following code.","pos":[18501,18622],"source":" For an example, see the **catch** statement and the **if** condition for the **oandaKey** variable in the following code."},{"content":"Implement the following helper methods.","pos":[26670,26709]},{"content":"These methods are specific to this example and aren't required for every provider.","pos":[26710,26792]},{"content":"Compile the <bpt id=\"p1\">**</bpt>ExchangeRateProviderOanda<ept id=\"p1\">**</ept> class.","pos":[31797,31845],"source":"Compile the **ExchangeRateProviderOanda** class."},{"content":"The provider will be run as part of a SysOperation.","pos":[31846,31897]},{"content":"It's helpful to understand the following framework classes and methods when you debug issues:","pos":[31898,31991]},{"content":"<bpt id=\"p1\">**</bpt>ExchangeRateProvide